Key Match Events: Australia won the fifth ODI to clinch the series 3-2.
Australia finished on 165-2 in 20.4 overs before rain stopped play.
Australia won by 49 runs under the DLS method.
The teams entered the final ODI tied at 2-2.
Josh Inglis celebrated stumping the wicket of England's Jacob Bethell.
Australia's Aaron Hardie celebrated taking the wicket of England's Will Jacks.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain stopped play at Bristol’s County Ground.
The match would have been abandoned as a no-result if Australia had not batted for 20 overs.
